Context:
The George Brown College offers a full-time gemmology certificate program, which is the only one in Ontario. They have over 250 partnerships with the jewellery industry that help facilitate field education opportunities and an annual jewellery exhibit and awards show. Their faculty are experts in the growing industry and students will learn using precious metals and gems with state-of-the-art tools and equipment. The college is one of North America's largest and best-equipped jewellery schools.

Barbara Heinrich, President of the American Jewelry Design Council, has praised the college for its quality of training provided to students. They offer a free Entry Advising service that matches academic skills, educational background, and career goals with options from the college's programs. For more detailed information about each jewellery program and the careers they lead to, an online information session recording is available featuring Paul McClure, Program Coordinator.

The contact information for the college is 416-415-2000 (voice) and 1-877-515-5559 (TTY). The email address is ask.george@georgebrown.ca, and they have a Social Media Hub for more information.

The information contained in the website is subject to change without notice. Students are responsible for verifying George Brown College fee requirements.
